  "texts": [
    "A possibility frame F = ⟨S, ⊑, {R i } i∈I, P ⟩ is filter-descriptive iff it is tight and for every proper filter F in F b, there is an x ∈ S such that F = P (x) = {X ∈ P | x ∈ X}.",
    "◁ Recall that tight implies ⊑-tight (Definition 4.32), which implies differentiated (Fact 4.33.3).The following two propositions show that filter-descriptive is indeed the notion we want.Proposition 5.39 (Filter-Descriptive Frames and BAOs).",
    "For any BAO A and possibility frame F:1.",
    "A g is filter-descriptive; 2.",
    "F is isomorphic to (F b) g iff F is filter-descriptive.Proof."
  ],
  "correct_citations": []
}